.TH SMTPD 8 "December 2024" "smtpd" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
smtpd \- Simple Mail Transfer Protocol server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smtpd
[\fI\,options\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smtpd
is a production-ready SMTP server designed for Linux systems.
It supports mail submission, delivery to maildir format,
authentication via PAM or shadow passwords, and TLS encryption.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c \fI\,file\/
fR
Specify configuration file (default: /etc/smtpd.conf)
.TP
.B \-d
Run in foreground (don't daemonize)
.TP
.B \-g
Generate self-signed SSL certificate
.TP
.B \-h
Display help and exit
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses the format \fBkey = value\fR.
See \fBsmtpd.conf\fR(5) for details.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/smtpd.conf
Default configuration file
.TP
.I /etc/pam.d/smtpd
PAM authentication configuration
.TP
.I /etc/ssl/certs/smtpd.crt
Default SSL certificate
.TP
.I /etc/ssl/private/smtpd.key
Default SSL private key
.TP
.I /var/mail
Default mail spool directory
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
SMTP (port 25), Submission (port 587), and SMTPS (port 465)
.IP \(bu 2
IPv4 and IPv6 support
.IP \(bu 2
STARTTLS and implicit TLS
.IP \(bu 2
AUTH PLAIN and AUTH LOGIN
.IP \(bu 2
PAM or shadow password authentication
.IP \(bu 2
Maildir format delivery
.IP \(bu 2
Message size limits
.SH SECURITY
Always use TLS in production. Set \fBallow_plaintext = 0\fR in
configuration to enforce encrypted connections.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pop3d (8),
.BR smtpd.conf (5),
.BR pam (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Production SMTP Server
